Artemisiospiza is a genus of birds in the American sparrow family, formally described by Klicka and Banks, 2011. It contains two species:

Sagebrush sparrow Artemisiospiza nevadensis
Bell's sparrow, Artemisiospiza belliThe two species historically comprised the sage sparrow complex, but were split in 2013 by the American Ornithological Society.
Both Artemisiospiza species inhabit dry areas of the western United States and northern Mexico.